706527f-c.title: Brooklyn: Rockaway Parkway - Avenue N
706527f-c.text:
(1)
Reskaway Parkway, west side, between Ave. N and Sea View Ave. This is the Jacobus Schenck house which stood upon a half-lot for which Martin R. Schenck held a patent in 1719 at which time he occupied the house. Mrs. J. Sehenck lived in it in 1873. It was razed about 191:.
About 1898.
Eugene L. Armbruster Cellection.
